---
title: Parmesan Crusted Tilapia with Parsley Potatoes and Carrots
description: Crispy parmesan-panko crust is the perfect topping for delicate tilapia. We’ve served it with potatoes and carrots in a garlicky herb butter for a Spring preview!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/54d220096ced6e811b8b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/54d220096ced6e811b8b4567.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: Mediterranean
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/parmesan-crusted-tilapia-54d220096ced6e811b8b4567
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 539 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 48 g
  protein: 47 g
  fiber: 8 g
servings: 2
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Place the @baby potatoes{12%oz} in a #pot{} of water
with a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cut any larger potatoes in half so they all
cook evenly. Bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer, and cook for ~{15-20%minutes},
until easily pierced with a knife. We'll be adding the carrots to the pot
later, so keep an eye on the time!

Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel the @carrot{1%large} and cut it into
sticks 2 inches long and 1/2-inches thick (as if you'd be dipping them in
hummus!) Zest and cut the @lemon{1%large} into wedges. Finely chop the
@parsley{1%bunch}.

In a #bowl{}, combine @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @dried oregano{1%tsp}, lemon
zest, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the garlic, and @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place the @tilapia fillets{2} on an oiled #baking sheet{}. Drizzle each tilapia
fillet with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper. Top each fillet
with half the panko mixture and press to adhere. Place in the oven and bake for
about ~{8%minutes}, until the fish is slightly opaque and easily flakes with a
fork.

> If you'd like, turn on the broiler and place the fillets under the heat source
> for about a minute, until the crust is golden brown. Make sure to keep an
> eye on it, it can burn quickly!

When the potatoes are almost ready, add the carrots to the #pot{} with the potatoes
and cook for about ~{5%minutes}, until crisp-tender. Drain and return to the pot.
Add the @butter{1%tbsp}, remaining garlic, and a pinch of parsley. Season with
salt and pepper. Cook, tossing, for a minute or two, until garlic is fragrant.

Serve the tilapia with the potatoes and carrots to the side. Finish with squeeze
of lemon and remaining parsley.